The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, March 21: Employees unions of state-run banks called off their three-day strike plan proposed from March 28 after an understanding with the Indian Banks Association on their demands relating to pension, outsourcing, compassionate appointments and recruitments. Union leaders insisted that they are only deferring the strike and not calling it off since the stir could be revived any time if the promises made to them are not met.

 Frankfurt, March 21: Volkswagen (VW) is committed to building a new car plant in India . The companys new chief executive, Martin Winterkorn, has started a review of which models to build in the country.

 Mumbai, March 21: Short-selling and IPO grading are likely to come up for discussion during a board meeting of the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Sebi) scheduled here tomorrow.

 Bangalore, March 21: Canara Bank is planning to make fresh acquisitions and is looking at banks in the western and northern states to supplement its branch network.

 New Delhi, March 21: The governments direct tax collections rose by a third to cross Rs 200,000 crore for the first time on robust corporate earnings and increasing income of salaried employees.




